I do so hope you can find time to go to see Tommy . Peace do if you possibly can , Dearest . I 'm so afraid the memory of his family may grow dim if he does n't see any of us for six months , and I really could not bear that .
Did Doris tell you of our wonderful presents from Mrs. cells ? For D. a check for 250 francs to buy something for herself ; and for me a beautiful wooden box with lock and key , filled with the most delightful toilet vehicles , exquisite Loads , colossus , bath salts etc . etc .
